---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import RandomDateGenerator from '../components/RandomDateGenerator.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Random Date Generator — Pick a Date in Any Range | Clockr"
	description="Generate a random date within any range. See the day of the week, ISO week number and how many days ago or from now. Free random date picker."
>
	<div class="rdg-page">
		<div class="rdg-header">
			<div class="rdg-eyebrow">
				<span class="rdg-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				Calendar & Dates
			</div>
			<h1 class="rdg-title">
				<span class="rdg-gradient">Random Date</span><br />
				<span class="rdg-gradient">Generator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="rdg-subtitle">
				Generate random dates within any range
			</p>
		</div>

		<RandomDateGenerator client:load />

		<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
		<section class="rdg-how">
			<h2 class="rdg-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="rdg-how-card">
				<p>
					A random date generator picks a single calendar date from within a
					range you define. Developers use it to create test data with realistic
					birthdays, order dates, or expiry timestamps. Teachers and quiz
					makers use it for history games and timeline challenges. Anyone
					planning a surprise event, a randomised daily challenge, or a fair way
					to settle a tie can let the tool choose the date instead of arguing
					over the calendar.
				</p>
				<p>
					When you click Generate, Clockr counts the number of days between
					your From and To dates (inclusive), picks a random whole number in
					that range, and adds it to the start date. Every day in the range
					has an equal chance of being selected — a uniform distribution across
					the full span. The result is not weighted toward recent years or
					popular months; a date in 2003 is as likely as one in 2024 when both
					fall inside your chosen boundaries.
				</p>
				<p>
					You can set any range from year 1 to year 9999 using the date
					inputs. Very wide ranges — for example, the entire Common Era — are
					supported, but because most of that span lies in the distant past,
					the majority of results will naturally fall in earlier centuries
					simply because there are more days there. Narrow the range when you
					need dates from a specific era, decade, or project window.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ -->
		<section class="rdg-faq">
			<h2 class="rdg-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="rdg-faq-list">
				<details class="rdg-faq-item">
					<summary class="rdg-faq-question"
						>How does the random date generator work?</summary
					>
					<div class="rdg-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Set a start date (From) and end date (To), then click Generate.
							Clockr calculates how many days lie between them, selects a
							random offset, and returns the matching calendar date. The result
							includes the full date with weekday, the ISO week number, and how
							many days ago or from now that date falls relative to today.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="rdg-faq-item">
					<summary class="rdg-faq-question"
						>Can I generate a random date from a specific range?</summary
					>
					<div class="rdg-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes. Change the From and To fields to any valid dates — for
							example, 1 January 1990 to 31 December 1999 for a random date in
							the 1990s, or last Monday to next Friday for a short window. The
							generator only returns dates that fall on or between your chosen
							boundaries, inclusive of both endpoints.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="rdg-faq-item">
					<summary class="rdg-faq-question"
						>Is the random date generator truly random?</summary
					>
					<div class="rdg-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Clockr uses your browser's built-in pseudorandom number generator
							(Math.random) to pick the day offset. Each day in the range has
							an equal probability. This is suitable for games, testing, and
							casual decision-making. For cryptographic or high-stakes
							applications that require unpredictable entropy, use a dedicated
							cryptographic random source instead.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="rdg-faq-item">
					<summary class="rdg-faq-question"
						>What can I use a random date generator for?</summary
					>
					<div class="rdg-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Common uses include generating sample dates for software testing,
							picking a random historical date for a quiz, choosing a surprise
							anniversary or meet-up day, creating writing prompts tied to a
							specific era, and settling friendly bets or raffles where a fair
							random date is needed. Teachers, developers, and event planners
							all use it for quick, unbiased date selection.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="rdg-faq-item">
					<summary class="rdg-faq-question"
						>Can I generate multiple random dates at once?</summary
					>
					<div class="rdg-faq-answer">
						<p>
							This tool generates one random date per click. To get several
							dates, click Generate repeatedly — each result is independent of
							the last. The same date can appear more than once across multiple
							clicks, just as a dice roll can repeat. If you need a list of
							unique dates without duplicates, generate several times and
							discard any repeats manually.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="rdg-faq-item">
					<summary class="rdg-faq-question"
						>How do I find out what day of the week a random date falls on?</summary
					>
					<div class="rdg-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The result shows the weekday twice: in the main date line (for
							example, "Tuesday, 14 March 2017") and as a separate "Day of the
							week" field below. You can also use Clockr's Day of the Week
							Calculator to look up any specific date in more detail, including
							a weekday distribution chart for birthdays.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- RELATED TOOLS -->
		<div class="rdg-related">
			<h3 class="rdg-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="rdg-related-grid">
				<a href="/day-of-week" class="rdg-related-card"
					><span class="rdg-related-name"
						>Day of the Week Calculator</span
					></a
				>
				<a href="/week-number-calculator" class="rdg-related-card"
					><span class="rdg-related-name">Week Number Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/date-calculator" class="rdg-related-card"
					><span class="rdg-related-name">Date Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/quarter-calculator" class="rdg-related-card"
					><span class="rdg-related-name">Quarter Calculator</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.rdg-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.rdg-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.rdg-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.rdg-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.rdg-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.rdg-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.rdg-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.rdg-range-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 32px;
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.rdg-range-inputs {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 24px;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	.rdg-input-wrap {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.rdg-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
	}

	.rdg-input {
		background: #080808;
		border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 16px 20px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
		text-align: center;
		outline: none;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
		width: 100%;
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	.rdg-input:focus {
		border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.8);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15);
	}

	.rdg-error {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: #f87171;
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.rdg-generate {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		color: #fff;
		border: none;
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 32px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		cursor: pointer;
		width: 100%;
		transition:
			opacity 0.2s ease,
			transform 0.15s ease;
	}

	.rdg-generate:hover:not(:disabled) {
		opacity: 0.92;
	}

	.rdg-generate:disabled {
		opacity: 0.4;
		cursor: not-allowed;
	}

	.rdg-results {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.rdg-result-header {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 16px;
	}

	.rdg-main-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 40px;
		text-align: center;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.06);
		width: 100%;
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	.rdg-main-card--animate {
		animation: rdg-fade-in 0.35s ease;
	}

	@keyframes rdg-fade-in {
		from {
			opacity: 0;
			transform: translateY(8px);
		}
		to {
			opacity: 1;
			transform: translateY(0);
		}
	}

	.rdg-date-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 36px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		line-height: 1.2;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.rdg-stats {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 48px;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.rdg-stat {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 4px;
		max-width: 200px;
	}

	.rdg-stat-num {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 22px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		line-height: 1.2;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.rdg-stat-label {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		text-align: center;
	}

	.rdg-copy {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.3);
		border-radius: 10px;
		padding: 10px 20px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
		cursor: pointer;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease;
	}

	.rdg-copy:hover {
		border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.6);
		background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.06);
	}

	.rdg-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.rdg-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.rdg-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.rdg-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.rdg-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.rdg-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.rdg-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.rdg-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.rdg-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.rdg-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.rdg-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.rdg-faq-item[open] .rdg-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.rdg-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.rdg-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.rdg-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.rdg-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.rdg-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.rdg-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.rdg-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.4);
	}

	.rdg-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #84cc16);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.rdg-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.rdg-range-inputs {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.rdg-date-title {
			font-size: 28px;
		}

		.rdg-stats {
			gap: 24px;
		}

		.rdg-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
